1
00:01:37,039 --> 00:01:40,120
[Born to Be Alive]

2
00:01:40,150 --> 00:01:43,150
[Episode 13]

3
00:01:49,509 --> 00:01:50,770
What's wrong, Sangba?

4
00:01:51,650 --> 00:01:52,229
Captain.

5
00:01:52,759 --> 00:01:53,539
Your wife is looking for you everywhere.

6
00:01:53,539 --> 00:01:54,620
She said there's an emergency at home

7
00:01:54,620 --> 00:01:55,780
and she wants you to go back.

8
00:01:55,780 --> 00:01:56,910
Didn't you tell her?

9
00:01:57,340 --> 00:01:58,509
I don't have time to go home.

10
00:01:58,509 --> 00:01:59,920
We need to head back immediately
to save people.

11
00:01:59,920 --> 00:02:00,560
She said you still have to go back.

12
00:02:00,560 --> 00:02:01,290
It is urgent.

13
00:02:04,650 --> 00:02:05,230
Captain.

14
00:02:06,170 --> 00:02:06,730
We're still preparing supplies.

15
00:02:06,730 --> 00:02:07,930
It'll take some time.

16
00:02:08,400 --> 00:02:09,330
Just go home now.

17
00:02:26,240 --> 00:02:27,670
Uncle, how are you?

18
00:02:28,079 --> 00:02:30,240
I'm good. Thank you.

19
00:02:30,900 --> 00:02:32,500
Deputy County Mayor Duojie.

20
00:02:32,530 --> 00:02:33,960
My mom isn't happy.

21
00:02:34,060 --> 00:02:35,740
She insisted we come find you.

22
00:02:35,840 --> 00:02:37,130
You said you'd pay us back in five months.

23
00:02:37,130 --> 00:02:38,560
It's been half a year now.

24
00:02:40,030 --> 00:02:41,020
I'm sorry.

25
00:02:41,960 --> 00:02:43,820
I'm really struggling right now.

26
00:02:44,090 --> 00:02:45,950
Can you give me a little more time?

27
00:02:46,210 --> 00:02:47,740
This can't wait any longer.

28
00:02:50,620 --> 00:02:52,060
You wrote this yourself.

29
00:02:52,560 --> 00:02:53,710
If this ten thousand yuan

30
00:02:53,710 --> 00:02:54,640
can't be repaid,

31
00:02:54,920 --> 00:02:55,960
then your livestock and your pasture

32
00:02:55,960 --> 00:02:57,690
will be taken as compensation.

33
00:02:58,250 --> 00:02:59,060
Duojie.

34
00:02:59,620 --> 00:03:00,690
We aren't

35
00:03:01,470 --> 00:03:03,690
rich people.

36
00:03:04,300 --> 00:03:06,830
We saved that money
by selling our livestock.

37
00:03:06,910 --> 00:03:08,560
Now Basang's house

38
00:03:09,190 --> 00:03:10,740
leaks when it rains.

39
00:03:10,910 --> 00:03:13,790
We need the money to fix the house.

40
00:03:14,370 --> 00:03:16,030
We can't wait any longer.

41
00:03:16,470 --> 00:03:17,500
I know.

42
00:03:18,520 --> 00:03:19,450
I'll get someone

43
00:03:19,750 --> 00:03:21,030
fix your house first.

44
00:03:22,030 --> 00:03:23,090
As for the money...

45
00:03:24,930 --> 00:03:25,329
Can you

46
00:03:25,340 --> 00:03:26,740
give me another month?

47
00:03:27,079 --> 00:03:27,970
I promise

48
00:03:28,079 --> 00:03:29,090
I'll pay you back next month.

49
00:03:29,090 --> 00:03:29,630
What if you

50
00:03:29,630 --> 00:03:31,090
go back on your word again?

51
00:03:42,680 --> 00:03:43,360
Then,

52
00:03:44,900 --> 00:03:46,250
you can take the livestock

53
00:03:46,250 --> 00:03:46,980
and pasture.

54
00:03:57,190 --> 00:03:57,970
Duojie.

55
00:03:58,280 --> 00:04:00,310
I've watched you grow up.

56
00:04:00,900 --> 00:04:02,360
Have you changed since you

57
00:04:02,650 --> 00:04:04,650
became the Deputy County Governor?

58
00:04:04,850 --> 00:04:05,940
A man's promise

59
00:04:06,780 --> 00:04:08,890
is like the scripture carved in stone.

60
00:04:08,890 --> 00:04:10,290
I hope you keep your word.

61
00:04:10,720 --> 00:04:13,240
Uncle, don't worry.

62
00:04:14,120 --> 00:04:16,180
I haven't changed. I'll keep my word.

63
00:04:17,370 --> 00:04:18,160
Alright.

64
00:04:18,630 --> 00:04:20,230
I'll trust you one more time.

65
00:04:20,560 --> 00:04:22,630
That's settled then. Let's go.

66
00:04:28,530 --> 00:04:30,270
Next month. Remember it.

67
00:04:30,330 --> 00:04:30,840
Okay.

68
00:04:31,740 --> 00:04:32,870
No need to see us out.

69
00:04:42,100 --> 00:04:44,600
I have to go back to the Uninhabited Zone
to save people.

70
00:04:44,600 --> 00:04:45,530
I'm leaving now.

71
00:04:46,540 --> 00:04:48,270
Are you just leaving like this?

72
00:04:48,570 --> 00:04:49,750
Our pasture,

73
00:04:50,070 --> 00:04:51,270
our cattle and sheep—

74
00:04:51,540 --> 00:04:53,650
Why didn't you tell me about this?

75
00:04:56,300 --> 00:04:57,370
If I don't go back,

76
00:04:59,180 --> 00:05:00,570
Bai Ju and my men

77
00:05:01,330 --> 00:05:02,390
will die in there.

78
00:05:43,570 --> 00:05:44,500
Dig faster.

79
00:05:44,740 --> 00:05:45,800
If it freezes over,

80
00:05:45,830 --> 00:05:47,630
we'll never be able to dig it out.

81
00:05:52,560 --> 00:05:53,330
Hurry up!

82
00:05:55,770 --> 00:05:57,100
I can't do this anymore.

83
00:05:57,450 --> 00:05:58,980
I really can't dig anymore.

84
00:06:02,430 --> 00:06:02,980
Stand up.

85
00:06:03,600 --> 00:06:04,600
Are you even a man?

86
00:06:05,220 --> 00:06:06,810
Zhacuo hasn't uttered a peep,

87
00:06:06,810 --> 00:06:07,500
yet he's digging faster

88
00:06:07,500 --> 00:06:08,000
than both of us

89
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:08,810
put together.

90
00:06:09,130 --> 00:06:09,930
Stand up, now.

91
00:06:11,630 --> 00:06:12,510
Zhacuo

92
00:06:13,190 --> 00:06:14,330
is like a yak.

93
00:06:14,930 --> 00:06:16,330
I can't compete with him.

94
00:06:18,270 --> 00:06:19,070
Zhacuo.

95
00:06:20,180 --> 00:06:20,920
Cuo.

96
00:06:21,680 --> 00:06:22,740
Rest a bit.

97
00:06:23,520 --> 00:06:24,700
Eat something.

98
00:06:28,870 --> 00:06:30,470
There's nothing left to eat.

99
00:06:42,159 --> 00:06:42,740
Zhacuo.

100
00:06:46,120 --> 00:06:46,870
Zhacuo.

101
00:06:58,000 --> 00:06:58,620
Zhacuo.

102
00:07:04,040 --> 00:07:04,680
Zhacuo!

103
00:07:05,320 --> 00:07:06,530
-Zhacuo!
-Zhacuo!

104
00:07:07,240 --> 00:07:07,970
Drink water.

105
00:07:08,560 --> 00:07:09,490
Drink, quickly.

106
00:07:11,920 --> 00:07:12,390
Have some more.

107
00:07:12,390 --> 00:07:12,920
Quick.

108
00:07:18,040 --> 00:07:19,170
He can't swallow it.

109
00:07:19,830 --> 00:07:20,830
What should we do?

110
00:07:25,770 --> 00:07:26,830
It's been two days.

111
00:07:27,540 --> 00:07:29,270
We at least had some flatbread.

112
00:07:30,270 --> 00:07:30,740
He gave all his flatbread

113
00:07:30,740 --> 00:07:31,720
to that child.

114
00:08:06,600 --> 00:08:07,660
What are you doing?

115
00:08:07,870 --> 00:08:08,930
What are you doing?

116
00:08:09,220 --> 00:08:10,280
What are you doing?

117
00:08:17,560 --> 00:08:19,020
Don't shoot the antelope!

118
00:08:19,370 --> 00:08:20,220
Step aside!

119
00:08:20,570 --> 00:08:21,250
If I don't do it,

120
00:08:21,250 --> 00:08:22,110
we will all die!

121
00:08:59,670 --> 00:09:00,410
Sangba!

122
00:09:00,790 --> 00:09:02,650
Load the rest onto your truck bed.

123
00:09:09,960 --> 00:09:11,160
Everything is ready.

124
00:09:11,240 --> 00:09:13,300
He Qingyuan is still having surgery.

125
00:09:13,370 --> 00:09:14,220
Can his arm be saved?

126
00:09:14,220 --> 00:09:14,770
I don't know.

127
00:09:14,770 --> 00:09:16,170
They won't let anyone in.

128
00:09:16,270 --> 00:09:17,030
Captain fell asleep

129
00:09:17,030 --> 00:09:18,390
shortly after leaving home.

130
00:09:18,390 --> 00:09:19,190
Let him sleep a bit longer.

131
00:09:19,190 --> 00:09:19,620
Okay.

132
00:09:31,770 --> 00:09:32,300
Captain.

133
00:09:33,050 --> 00:09:34,310
Why didn't you wake me?

134
00:09:42,030 --> 00:09:43,230
Is everything ready?

135
00:09:43,820 --> 00:09:44,510
Yes.

136
00:09:45,700 --> 00:09:46,630
Load up quickly.

137
00:09:46,940 --> 00:09:47,250
Okay.

138
00:09:47,250 --> 00:09:47,600
Okay.

139
00:10:02,720 --> 00:10:03,500
Director Zhang.

140
00:10:03,500 --> 00:10:05,160
The Mountain Patrol is ready.

141
00:10:05,240 --> 00:10:06,130
Deputy County Mayor Duo asked—

142
00:10:06,130 --> 00:10:07,050
Tell him

143
00:10:07,150 --> 00:10:08,750
I can't guarantee anything.

144
00:10:09,500 --> 00:10:10,230
Understood.

145
00:10:11,010 --> 00:10:11,960
He's asked

146
00:10:12,110 --> 00:10:12,790
if there's anything

147
00:10:12,790 --> 00:10:13,920
you want to tell him.

148
00:10:20,130 --> 00:10:21,170
No matter what,

149
00:10:22,510 --> 00:10:23,790
bring Bai Ju back.

150
00:11:23,500 --> 00:11:24,290
Are you sure

151
00:11:25,050 --> 00:11:25,890
this is

152
00:11:26,580 --> 00:11:27,780
the right direction?

153
00:11:37,510 --> 00:11:38,600
Yes.

154
00:11:39,890 --> 00:11:41,000
Then how long

155
00:11:41,720 --> 00:11:43,050
until we reach the road?

156
00:11:44,080 --> 00:11:45,480
If it keeps snowing,

157
00:11:48,510 --> 00:11:49,640
it'll take two days.

158
00:12:30,360 --> 00:12:31,620
Captain, let me drive.

159
00:12:31,660 --> 00:12:32,220
No need.

160
00:13:36,290 --> 00:13:37,650
If I can't walk anymore,

161
00:13:40,130 --> 00:13:41,130
shoot me to death.

162
00:13:47,130 --> 00:13:48,240
What are you talking about?

163
00:13:48,240 --> 00:13:49,040
It's the same.

164
00:13:51,500 --> 00:13:52,960
If you can't walk anymore,

165
00:13:54,360 --> 00:13:55,690
I'll shoot you to death.

166
00:13:59,340 --> 00:14:00,740
Freezing slowly to death

167
00:14:03,440 --> 00:14:04,550
is too painful.

168
00:14:36,580 --> 00:14:37,130
Captain.

169
00:15:27,530 --> 00:15:28,390
Shao Yunfei.

170
00:15:30,320 --> 00:15:31,240
Shao Yunfei!

171
00:15:32,980 --> 00:15:33,770
I'm tired.

172
00:15:34,770 --> 00:15:35,900
I don't want to talk.

173
00:15:36,980 --> 00:15:38,220
Am I seeing things?

174
00:15:39,770 --> 00:15:40,750
Why do I see

175
00:15:42,150 --> 00:15:43,510
a truck up ahead?

176
00:16:30,410 --> 00:16:30,940
Let's go.

177
00:16:31,320 --> 00:16:32,450
Check the back of it.

178
00:17:03,600 --> 00:17:04,609
It's out of gas.

179
00:17:06,700 --> 00:17:08,300
Even with gas, it won't move.

180
00:17:09,349 --> 00:17:11,079
It's completely rusted solid.

181
00:17:18,270 --> 00:17:18,800
Let's go.

182
00:17:21,380 --> 00:17:21,910
Let's go.

183
00:17:22,530 --> 00:17:23,730
I can't walk anymore.

184
00:17:28,140 --> 00:17:29,220
Then you rest a bit.

185
00:17:30,070 --> 00:17:30,980
I'll go

186
00:17:32,090 --> 00:17:32,950
drag them over.

187
00:17:39,350 --> 00:17:39,960
Bai Ju.

188
00:17:41,250 --> 00:17:42,240
What?

189
00:17:44,880 --> 00:17:45,900
What is that?

190
00:17:46,810 --> 00:17:47,500
Look!

191
00:17:58,350 --> 00:17:59,550
A blizzard is coming.

192
00:18:00,240 --> 00:18:00,790
Let's go!

193
00:18:01,110 --> 00:18:01,910
Hurry!

194
00:18:19,420 --> 00:18:20,270
Hurry!

195
00:19:03,700 --> 00:19:04,830
Why are we stopping?

196
00:19:05,330 --> 00:19:06,100
Captain, it's snowing.

197
00:19:06,100 --> 00:19:07,010
Let's set up camp here.

198
00:19:07,010 --> 00:19:08,240
Get in. Keep moving.

199
00:19:08,260 --> 00:19:09,050
If the snow gets heavier,

200
00:19:09,050 --> 00:19:10,380
we might get separated.

201
00:19:10,380 --> 00:19:11,270
If we lose contact,

202
00:19:11,270 --> 00:19:12,400
it'll be dangerous.

203
00:19:40,290 --> 00:19:41,440
You keep it.

204
00:19:42,070 --> 00:19:43,000
I'm not thirsty.

205
00:19:44,260 --> 00:19:45,460
If it freezes later,

206
00:19:45,580 --> 00:19:47,180
you won't be able to drink it.

207
00:19:47,240 --> 00:19:47,790
Quick.

208
00:20:11,980 --> 00:20:14,640
Will you ever come back
to the Uninhabited Zone?

209
00:20:16,050 --> 00:20:17,380
Do we even have a future?

210
00:20:20,920 --> 00:20:22,350
Do you regret staying?

211
00:20:25,900 --> 00:20:27,610
Not at all.

212
00:20:28,930 --> 00:20:30,640
My only regret

213
00:20:33,180 --> 00:20:33,790
is

214
00:20:36,140 --> 00:20:37,350
not coming sooner

215
00:20:38,570 --> 00:20:39,550
to get your story

216
00:20:42,110 --> 00:20:43,160
written down

217
00:20:43,530 --> 00:20:45,060
and share it with the world.

218
00:20:47,700 --> 00:20:49,460
By your definition,

219
00:20:51,450 --> 00:20:52,500
I guess that makes us

220
00:20:52,500 --> 00:20:53,310
kind of noble.

221
00:20:57,620 --> 00:20:58,680
Congratulations.

222
00:21:00,020 --> 00:21:02,150
You're going to be a noble journalist.

223
00:21:04,900 --> 00:21:06,720
I wasn't exaggerating.

224
00:21:10,380 --> 00:21:11,580
I never thought about

225
00:21:12,440 --> 00:21:13,770
how others would see me

226
00:21:15,250 --> 00:21:16,270
or us.

227
00:21:21,220 --> 00:21:22,180
I just think

228
00:21:23,380 --> 00:21:24,710
that I've been to places

229
00:21:24,940 --> 00:21:25,720
where no one else

230
00:21:25,720 --> 00:21:26,740
has ever been

231
00:21:28,460 --> 00:21:29,270
and experienced stories

232
00:21:29,270 --> 00:21:30,800
others have never heard of.

233
00:21:33,900 --> 00:21:35,530
Even though it feels like

234
00:21:37,150 --> 00:21:38,350
something's missing

235
00:21:42,110 --> 00:21:44,660
ending it this way,

236
00:21:47,750 --> 00:21:48,550
at least

237
00:21:51,960 --> 00:21:53,690
I managed to get one thing done.

238
00:21:56,530 --> 00:21:57,530
It'll be worth it.

239
00:21:57,960 --> 00:21:59,850
It... It'll be worth it.

240
00:22:03,070 --> 00:22:04,070
My parents

241
00:22:04,760 --> 00:22:06,590
died in the blizzard.

242
00:22:08,290 --> 00:22:09,750
I wonder back then,

243
00:22:10,110 --> 00:22:11,300
how they felt

244
00:22:12,640 --> 00:22:14,240
and what they were thinking.

245
00:22:14,900 --> 00:22:16,010
Did they think

246
00:22:17,010 --> 00:22:18,480
their lives were worth it?

247
00:22:23,200 --> 00:22:23,800
They were.

248
00:22:26,140 --> 00:22:27,670
Because they they made sure

249
00:22:29,770 --> 00:22:30,640
you survive.

250
00:22:36,290 --> 00:22:37,270
Right now,

251
00:22:38,960 --> 00:22:40,160
I really want to live.

252
00:22:43,550 --> 00:22:45,010
It's not worth dying here.

253
00:22:48,460 --> 00:22:49,680
I really want to know

254
00:22:52,180 --> 00:22:54,070
how Duojie's stomach is doing,

255
00:22:56,010 --> 00:22:58,980
and whether He's arm can be saved.

256
00:23:01,440 --> 00:23:03,240
And before I left home this time,

257
00:23:05,510 --> 00:23:06,630
I didn't get the chance

258
00:23:06,630 --> 00:23:08,290
to say a proper goodbye to Mom,

259
00:23:09,240 --> 00:23:10,000
Shao,

260
00:23:11,270 --> 00:23:13,270
and Bai Ji.

261
00:23:27,680 --> 00:23:29,660
Shao... Shao Yunfei.

262
00:23:30,450 --> 00:23:32,440
Shao... Shao Yunfei.

263
00:23:37,530 --> 00:23:38,310
Shao Yunfei.

264
00:23:39,250 --> 00:23:40,070
Shao Yunfei!

265
00:23:40,570 --> 00:23:41,300
Shao Yunfei.

266
00:23:42,050 --> 00:23:42,780
Shao Yunfei.

267
00:23:43,830 --> 00:23:44,690
Say something.

268
00:23:45,640 --> 00:23:46,570
Wake up.

269
00:23:46,590 --> 00:23:47,520
You can't sleep.

270
00:23:48,180 --> 00:23:49,610
If you sleep, you won't wake up again.

271
00:23:49,610 --> 00:23:50,480
Wake up.

272
00:23:50,620 --> 00:23:51,530
Wake up.

273
00:23:55,570 --> 00:23:56,830
-It's hot.
-What are you doing?

274
00:23:56,830 --> 00:23:57,570
Don't take it off.

275
00:23:57,570 --> 00:23:58,100
It's hot.

276
00:23:58,110 --> 00:23:59,110
Don't take it off.

277
00:24:00,140 --> 00:24:00,750
Don't take it off!

278
00:24:00,750 --> 00:24:01,330
It's hot.

279
00:24:01,440 --> 00:24:02,440
Don't take it off!

280
00:24:02,770 --> 00:24:03,680
Don't take it off!

281
00:24:03,680 --> 00:24:04,610
Before freezing to death,

282
00:24:04,610 --> 00:24:06,210
people go into hypothermia.

283
00:24:06,690 --> 00:24:08,200
The body starts to send false signals

284
00:24:08,200 --> 00:24:09,410
and feels an intense heat.

285
00:24:09,410 --> 00:24:10,830
Don't take it off. Don't take it off!

286
00:24:10,830 --> 00:24:11,310
Bai Ju.

287
00:24:12,000 --> 00:24:12,760
The heat...

288
00:24:13,380 --> 00:24:15,310
The heat feels worse than the cold.

289
00:24:18,660 --> 00:24:20,110
You were right.

290
00:24:21,240 --> 00:24:22,840
Slowly freezing to death...

291
00:24:22,960 --> 00:24:25,350
Slowly freezing to death is unbearable.

292
00:24:32,500 --> 00:24:33,140
Bai Ju.

293
00:24:35,510 --> 00:24:36,200
Bai Ju.

294
00:24:37,280 --> 00:24:38,760
Can you shoot straight?

295
00:24:53,550 --> 00:24:54,050
Yes.

296
00:28:05,330 --> 00:28:06,980
I'm here!

297
00:28:08,270 --> 00:28:10,420
I'm here!

298
00:28:11,720 --> 00:28:13,010
I'm here!

299
00:28:13,270 --> 00:28:14,660
I'm here!

300
00:28:14,960 --> 00:28:17,010
I... I'm here!

301
00:30:30,070 --> 00:30:31,050
Captain!

302
00:30:31,070 --> 00:30:32,050
Look back!

303
00:30:32,750 --> 00:30:33,740
It's Bai!

304
00:31:12,380 --> 00:31:13,240
I'm here.

305
00:31:14,240 --> 00:31:15,220
I'm here.

306
00:31:16,500 --> 00:31:17,480
I'm here.

307
00:31:23,140 --> 00:31:24,290
I'm here!

308
00:31:24,710 --> 00:31:25,800
I'm here!

309
00:31:27,640 --> 00:31:28,850
I'm here!

310
00:31:29,960 --> 00:31:31,070
I'm here!

311
00:31:31,750 --> 00:31:33,090
I'm here!

312
00:31:34,010 --> 00:31:35,640
I'm here!

313
00:31:37,200 --> 00:31:38,960
I'm here!

314
00:31:46,640 --> 00:31:47,810
I'm here!

315
00:31:48,960 --> 00:31:50,140
I'm here!

316
00:32:04,460 --> 00:32:05,250
Bai Ju!

317
00:32:07,660 --> 00:32:08,290
Bai Ju!

318
00:32:14,200 --> 00:32:14,770
Bai Ju.

319
00:32:17,530 --> 00:32:18,320
I found you.

320
00:32:20,660 --> 00:32:21,180
Bai Ju.

321
00:32:38,360 --> 00:32:39,160
It's okay now.

322
00:32:39,440 --> 00:32:40,110
I found you.

323
00:32:40,530 --> 00:32:41,250
I found you.

324
00:32:42,380 --> 00:32:43,160
I found you.

325
00:33:25,000 --> 00:33:25,680
Breakfast.

326
00:33:32,820 --> 00:33:34,420
Is this enough to fill you up?

327
00:33:36,220 --> 00:33:37,080
I'm not hungry.

328
00:33:47,530 --> 00:33:48,110
Thanks.

329
00:33:49,690 --> 00:33:50,420
Wait.

330
00:33:58,100 --> 00:33:58,930
Just put it here.

331
00:33:58,930 --> 00:33:59,930
I'll eat it later.

332
00:34:19,530 --> 00:34:21,060
You're quite fashionable.

333
00:34:25,360 --> 00:34:26,090
It's Shao's.

334
00:34:26,350 --> 00:34:27,139
No, I mean

335
00:34:27,170 --> 00:34:28,780
the candy you're eating

336
00:34:28,840 --> 00:34:29,830
is quite fashionable.

337
00:34:29,830 --> 00:34:30,960
That's also Shao's.

338
00:34:38,190 --> 00:34:39,340
Why are you here?

339
00:34:39,380 --> 00:34:42,510
Shouldn't you be inside, lying down
and getting your IV?

340
00:34:42,920 --> 00:34:44,719
I've been sleeping for two days.

341
00:34:45,010 --> 00:34:46,090
If I keep lying there,

342
00:34:46,090 --> 00:34:47,360
I'll get bedsores.

343
00:34:47,760 --> 00:34:48,690
If it weren't for my mom

344
00:34:48,690 --> 00:34:50,150
insisting I finish the IV,

345
00:34:50,480 --> 00:34:52,340
I'd be back with the patrol by now.

346
00:34:57,010 --> 00:34:58,110
I wonder

347
00:34:58,300 --> 00:35:00,030
how that calf is doing.

348
00:35:00,190 --> 00:35:00,820
Duojie gave it

349
00:35:00,820 --> 00:35:02,620
to the nearby herdsmen to raise.

350
00:35:04,120 --> 00:35:05,350
Once a calf picks up

351
00:35:05,370 --> 00:35:06,390
a human scent,

352
00:35:07,410 --> 00:35:09,670
it's hard for it to rejoin the wild flock.

353
00:35:10,280 --> 00:35:12,080
We have to wait two or three years

354
00:35:12,510 --> 00:35:13,640
and try to release it

355
00:35:13,710 --> 00:35:14,760
once it's grown.

356
00:35:15,560 --> 00:35:17,650
If you don't want to chat with me,

357
00:35:17,890 --> 00:35:18,830
don't force it.

358
00:35:26,550 --> 00:35:28,640
I'm just here to sit in the sun with you.

359
00:35:28,640 --> 00:35:29,340
When the IV is done,

360
00:35:29,340 --> 00:35:31,140
I'll take the needle out for you.

361
00:35:33,110 --> 00:35:34,130
It's not finished yet?

362
00:35:34,130 --> 00:35:35,330
Auntie, you're back.

363
00:35:36,300 --> 00:35:37,630
We're making dumplings for lunch.

364
00:35:37,630 --> 00:35:38,610
Bai Shao went to buy meat.

365
00:35:38,610 --> 00:35:40,010
Okay. Thank you, Auntie.

366
00:35:43,360 --> 00:35:44,160
What's wrong?

367
00:35:47,210 --> 00:35:48,080
It's just

368
00:35:48,320 --> 00:35:49,580
that I have frostbite.

369
00:35:50,010 --> 00:35:51,140
It hurts and itches.

370
00:35:51,670 --> 00:35:52,800
I bumped it just now.

371
00:36:00,780 --> 00:36:02,040
This chunk looks good.

372
00:36:03,250 --> 00:36:04,510
This isn't grass-fed.

373
00:36:08,090 --> 00:36:09,090
You can tell that?

374
00:36:11,220 --> 00:36:12,480
Just life experience.

375
00:36:13,690 --> 00:36:14,950
You have so much life experience.

376
00:36:14,950 --> 00:36:15,550
Sometimes my mom

377
00:36:15,550 --> 00:36:16,950
even buys the wrong kind.

378
00:36:17,300 --> 00:36:18,230
This one is good.

379
00:36:19,320 --> 00:36:21,150
I guarantee this is grass-fed.

380
00:36:22,210 --> 00:36:22,800
How much?

381
00:36:23,590 --> 00:36:24,450
Five yuan a jin.

382
00:36:24,820 --> 00:36:26,080
Okay, give me two jins.

383
00:36:26,900 --> 00:36:28,030
What about this chunk?

384
00:36:28,030 --> 00:36:29,000
3.5 yuan a jin.

385
00:36:29,570 --> 00:36:30,430
3.5 is fine.

386
00:36:30,460 --> 00:36:31,390
Give me two jins.

387
00:36:31,620 --> 00:36:32,120
Wait.

388
00:36:32,730 --> 00:36:33,540
Buy the good one.

389
00:36:33,540 --> 00:36:34,140
It's on me.

390
00:36:34,260 --> 00:36:34,730
No need.

391
00:36:35,280 --> 00:36:36,380
Good quality or bad,

392
00:36:36,380 --> 00:36:37,380
anyway, the reporter from

393
00:36:37,380 --> 00:36:38,260
the provincial capital

394
00:36:38,260 --> 00:36:40,390
won't be able to taste the difference.

395
00:36:40,750 --> 00:36:41,780
Mince it a bit for me.

396
00:36:41,780 --> 00:36:43,040
I'm making dumplings.

397
00:36:43,500 --> 00:36:44,050
Okay.

398
00:36:44,810 --> 00:36:46,550
That doesn't feel right, does it?

399
00:36:46,550 --> 00:36:47,110
No matter what,

400
00:36:47,110 --> 00:36:48,030
he is a guest.

401
00:36:48,500 --> 00:36:49,870
And I heard from my dad

402
00:36:50,190 --> 00:36:51,050
that the reporter

403
00:36:51,050 --> 00:36:52,570
is a bit stubborn

404
00:36:52,670 --> 00:36:54,070
but quite professional.

405
00:36:54,550 --> 00:36:54,960
What does that

406
00:36:54,960 --> 00:36:55,960
have to do with us?

407
00:36:58,090 --> 00:36:58,800
Anyway,

408
00:36:59,160 --> 00:37:00,820
he's leaving sooner or later.

409
00:37:01,100 --> 00:37:03,000
So, there's no need
to give him the good stuff.

410
00:37:03,000 --> 00:37:03,850
That's true.

411
00:37:04,340 --> 00:37:05,740
Even if we try to be nice to him,

412
00:37:05,740 --> 00:37:06,340
he might not

413
00:37:06,340 --> 00:37:07,280
appreciate it.

414
00:37:08,940 --> 00:37:09,750
Bai Shao,

415
00:37:09,850 --> 00:37:11,240
you've really thought this through.

416
00:37:11,240 --> 00:37:13,410
Does this count as social experience?

417
00:37:13,940 --> 00:37:15,270
I need to learn from you.

418
00:37:16,150 --> 00:37:16,910
What kind of

419
00:37:16,940 --> 00:37:18,600
"social experience" is that?

420
00:37:18,860 --> 00:37:20,170
I just think

421
00:37:20,610 --> 00:37:21,780
people here

422
00:37:22,070 --> 00:37:23,320
are too honest.

423
00:37:23,660 --> 00:37:24,580
It's easy for outsiders

424
00:37:24,580 --> 00:37:25,910
to take advantage of us.

425
00:37:26,630 --> 00:37:27,280
Exactly.

426
00:37:27,800 --> 00:37:28,400
I don't like

427
00:37:28,400 --> 00:37:30,200
people from big cities, either.

428
00:37:32,330 --> 00:37:32,960
Going away for school

429
00:37:32,960 --> 00:37:34,570
is just to broaden my horizons.

430
00:37:34,570 --> 00:37:35,310
If my parents

431
00:37:35,340 --> 00:37:36,000
didn't force me,

432
00:37:36,000 --> 00:37:36,940
I wouldn't go.

433
00:37:39,340 --> 00:37:40,690
I actually think

434
00:37:41,150 --> 00:37:42,110
Uncle Lin and Auntie Zhu

435
00:37:42,110 --> 00:37:43,310
have good foresight.

436
00:37:45,150 --> 00:37:46,500
I still like it here.

437
00:37:47,040 --> 00:37:48,820
People around here
are simple and down-to-earth.

438
00:37:48,820 --> 00:37:49,950
Unlike the outside,

439
00:37:49,970 --> 00:37:51,030
where you have to

440
00:37:51,210 --> 00:37:52,710
scheme against each other.

441
00:37:52,710 --> 00:37:53,440
Look,

442
00:37:53,730 --> 00:37:54,650
I'm not

443
00:37:55,400 --> 00:37:56,590
very sharp socially, either.

444
00:37:56,590 --> 00:37:58,590
I can't even beat you at buying meat.

445
00:38:00,140 --> 00:38:00,840
Is the meat ready?

446
00:38:00,840 --> 00:38:01,260
Yes.

447
00:38:01,360 --> 00:38:01,910
Thanks.

448
00:38:06,220 --> 00:38:08,080
I've discussed it with my family.

449
00:38:08,130 --> 00:38:09,840
I'll come back as soon as I graduate.

450
00:38:09,840 --> 00:38:10,530
When our county

451
00:38:10,530 --> 00:38:11,860
establishes the mining company,

452
00:38:11,860 --> 00:38:13,660
it'll set up a branch in Tianduo.

453
00:38:13,780 --> 00:38:14,110
Then,

454
00:38:14,110 --> 00:38:15,440
I'll go work in the city.

455
00:38:16,040 --> 00:38:17,300
People from our family will be

456
00:38:17,300 --> 00:38:18,960
the first batch of employees.

457
00:38:19,330 --> 00:38:20,160
Our family?

458
00:38:23,500 --> 00:38:24,710
Who knows if the mining company

459
00:38:24,710 --> 00:38:26,310
will even get off the ground.

460
00:38:26,340 --> 00:38:27,260
Deputy County Mayor Duo

461
00:38:27,260 --> 00:38:28,090
has always been against

462
00:38:28,090 --> 00:38:28,750
the mining.

463
00:38:29,990 --> 00:38:31,250
Let them discuss that.

464
00:38:31,920 --> 00:38:32,790
Let me carry that for you.

465
00:38:32,790 --> 00:38:34,120
No need. It's not heavy.

466
00:38:36,190 --> 00:38:37,340
When we get back to your house,

467
00:38:37,340 --> 00:38:39,070
teach me how to make dumplings.

468
00:38:42,500 --> 00:38:42,870
Or

469
00:38:42,900 --> 00:38:44,110
I can just help you out.

470
00:38:44,110 --> 00:38:44,610
Actually, I don't know

471
00:38:44,610 --> 00:38:45,460
what I can do.

472
00:38:49,010 --> 00:38:49,940
Maybe next time.

473
00:38:51,030 --> 00:38:51,460
We have a guest

474
00:38:51,460 --> 00:38:52,570
today.

475
00:38:52,710 --> 00:38:54,170
Plus, Bai Ju

476
00:38:54,190 --> 00:38:56,120
hasn't fully recovered from her injury.

477
00:38:56,120 --> 00:38:57,850
So, it's not convenient today.

478
00:38:59,090 --> 00:39:00,220
Alright, it's fine.

479
00:39:05,740 --> 00:39:06,530
When we first came here,

480
00:39:06,530 --> 00:39:07,860
there was no courtyard.

481
00:39:08,350 --> 00:39:09,910
There weren't even walls.

482
00:39:11,720 --> 00:39:12,640
The herdsmen

483
00:39:12,670 --> 00:39:14,030
set up tents for us.

484
00:39:14,670 --> 00:39:15,520
Unlike those small

485
00:39:15,520 --> 00:39:16,030
modern tents,

486
00:39:16,030 --> 00:39:17,430
those tents were the size

487
00:39:18,530 --> 00:39:19,430
of a house.

488
00:39:19,650 --> 00:39:20,530
We worked and lived

489
00:39:20,530 --> 00:39:21,150
all

490
00:39:21,170 --> 00:39:21,960
in there.

491
00:39:22,300 --> 00:39:23,650
So the director and the staff

492
00:39:23,650 --> 00:39:25,190
all lived and ate together.

493
00:39:26,260 --> 00:39:27,730
The atmosphere was actually quite nice.

494
00:39:27,730 --> 00:39:28,050
Back then,

495
00:39:28,050 --> 00:39:29,710
there wasn't even a director.

496
00:39:29,730 --> 00:39:30,400
Just one teacher,

497
00:39:30,400 --> 00:39:31,530
leading a few of us.

498
00:39:32,190 --> 00:39:33,550
That teacher

499
00:39:34,010 --> 00:39:36,410
was a graduate of Sichuan Medical College.

500
00:39:36,820 --> 00:39:37,630
Later, when he got older,

501
00:39:37,630 --> 00:39:38,400
he went back.

502
00:39:39,130 --> 00:39:40,560
Was there anything back then

503
00:39:40,560 --> 00:39:43,090
that you found particularly unforgettable?

504
00:39:47,260 --> 00:39:47,660
Well,

505
00:39:47,690 --> 00:39:48,790
I picked up a girl

506
00:39:48,820 --> 00:39:50,220
while I was out on rounds.

507
00:39:54,090 --> 00:39:56,220
There was also a doctor from Shanghai.

508
00:39:56,280 --> 00:39:57,280
He performed

509
00:39:57,300 --> 00:39:58,270
an appendectomy on himself.

510
00:39:58,270 --> 00:39:59,730
On himself?

511
00:40:00,110 --> 00:40:01,970
You haven't heard of that, right?

512
00:40:02,400 --> 00:40:03,170
I remember now.

513
00:40:03,170 --> 00:40:04,170
It was

514
00:40:04,280 --> 00:40:05,280
Uncle Sun, right?

515
00:40:05,360 --> 00:40:06,130
Yes.

516
00:40:07,050 --> 00:40:08,610
I guess back then,

517
00:40:08,800 --> 00:40:09,210
that was

518
00:40:09,210 --> 00:40:11,210
the only case in the entire country.

519
00:40:11,810 --> 00:40:12,480
At that time,

520
00:40:12,480 --> 00:40:14,350
he was out on rounds in the pastoral area,

521
00:40:14,350 --> 00:40:16,550
and there were no other doctors around.

522
00:40:16,730 --> 00:40:17,570
His appendix pain

523
00:40:17,570 --> 00:40:18,980
was unbearable.

524
00:40:19,000 --> 00:40:20,800
So right there on the grassland,

525
00:40:20,820 --> 00:40:21,820
he set up a mirror,

526
00:40:22,070 --> 00:40:23,400
used local anesthesia,

527
00:40:23,570 --> 00:40:25,400
and cut it out himself.

528
00:40:30,540 --> 00:40:31,250
I thought

529
00:40:31,280 --> 00:40:32,520
the Mountain Patrol guys
were already hardcore,

530
00:40:32,520 --> 00:40:33,280
but I didn't expect

531
00:40:33,280 --> 00:40:35,730
the people from your hospital
to be even tougher.

532
00:40:35,730 --> 00:40:36,670
Alright,

533
00:40:36,910 --> 00:40:38,050
stop flattering my mom.

534
00:40:38,050 --> 00:40:39,070
Really.

535
00:40:39,170 --> 00:40:41,170
People here really are impressive.

536
00:40:41,230 --> 00:40:42,190
Because this place

537
00:40:42,190 --> 00:40:42,940
is where people are truly

538
00:40:42,940 --> 00:40:44,380
tested and forged.

539
00:40:45,090 --> 00:40:45,960
So many people who left here

540
00:40:45,960 --> 00:40:46,660
later on

541
00:40:46,690 --> 00:40:48,320
went on to do really well.

542
00:40:49,450 --> 00:40:50,140
By the way,

543
00:40:50,360 --> 00:40:52,360
your mom works at
the Cultural Department, right?

544
00:40:52,360 --> 00:40:53,130
Yes.

545
00:40:53,960 --> 00:40:56,250
The former Deputy Party Secretary

546
00:40:56,460 --> 00:40:57,460
of Quduo Township

547
00:40:57,510 --> 00:40:58,960
was a section chief sent down

548
00:40:58,960 --> 00:41:00,690
from the Provincial Department of Culture.

549
00:41:00,690 --> 00:41:01,210
He served in a temporary position here

550
00:41:01,210 --> 00:41:02,320
for two years.

551
00:41:02,440 --> 00:41:03,670
Not long after he went back,

552
00:41:03,670 --> 00:41:06,110
he was promoted to full division-level,
skipping ranks.

553
00:41:06,110 --> 00:41:07,400
I really think these people

554
00:41:07,400 --> 00:41:08,480
are just

555
00:41:08,570 --> 00:41:09,840
capable and able to endure hardship,

556
00:41:09,840 --> 00:41:10,400
right?

557
00:41:10,980 --> 00:41:11,690
Shao,

558
00:41:12,190 --> 00:41:14,010
you're quite capable, too.

559
00:41:14,180 --> 00:41:15,740
You've been with the Mountain Patrol

560
00:41:15,740 --> 00:41:17,600
for so long without complaining.

561
00:41:18,910 --> 00:41:19,680
Have you ever thought about

562
00:41:19,680 --> 00:41:21,340
taking a temporary post here?

563
00:41:25,570 --> 00:41:26,820
Grassroots experience

564
00:41:26,820 --> 00:41:28,030
is very important,

565
00:41:29,070 --> 00:41:30,110
especially for someone

566
00:41:30,110 --> 00:41:31,440
in journalism like you.

567
00:41:31,880 --> 00:41:33,020
If you take a post here

568
00:41:33,020 --> 00:41:33,720
and work for a few years,

569
00:41:33,720 --> 00:41:34,280
when you go back,

570
00:41:34,280 --> 00:41:35,570
your promotion speed

571
00:41:36,610 --> 00:41:38,010
will be totally different

572
00:41:38,010 --> 00:41:39,670
compared to your colleagues.

573
00:41:40,860 --> 00:41:41,820
And another thing,

574
00:41:41,820 --> 00:41:42,950
that doctor

575
00:41:43,330 --> 00:41:44,090
who came here

576
00:41:44,120 --> 00:41:45,740
to provide support.

577
00:41:45,780 --> 00:41:46,940
After working for a few years,
he went back.

578
00:41:46,940 --> 00:41:47,400
But when he left,

579
00:41:47,400 --> 00:41:48,710
he didn't go back alone.

580
00:41:48,710 --> 00:41:49,590
He took his partner

581
00:41:49,590 --> 00:41:50,470
back with him.

582
00:41:51,490 --> 00:41:52,510
He even got

583
00:41:52,540 --> 00:41:53,740
his marriage sorted.

584
00:41:55,300 --> 00:41:56,520
Of course, there was no wedding banquet.

585
00:41:56,520 --> 00:41:58,250
Conditions were limited here.

586
00:41:58,800 --> 00:42:00,050
But we all shared

587
00:42:00,190 --> 00:42:01,570
a whole sheep together,

588
00:42:01,590 --> 00:42:03,340
and it was a blast!

589
00:42:04,320 --> 00:42:04,610
Auntie,

590
00:42:04,610 --> 00:42:06,000
about this temporary posting,

591
00:42:06,000 --> 00:42:07,080
I… I…

592
00:42:07,890 --> 00:42:08,880
I really haven't thought about it before.

593
00:42:08,880 --> 00:42:10,540
Alright, stop interviewing.

594
00:42:10,710 --> 00:42:11,630
The dumplings are ready.

595
00:42:11,630 --> 00:42:12,390
Go wash your hands.

596
00:42:12,390 --> 00:42:13,400
Well, Auntie.

597
00:42:13,430 --> 00:42:14,380
I'll go wash my

598
00:42:14,430 --> 00:42:15,410
fingers.

599
00:42:25,180 --> 00:42:25,660
Mom,

600
00:42:26,260 --> 00:42:27,860
why did you tell him all that?

601
00:42:28,160 --> 00:42:29,290
It was an interview.

602
00:42:29,780 --> 00:42:31,030
I think I spoke well.

603
00:42:33,810 --> 00:42:35,140
The first part was fine.

604
00:42:35,900 --> 00:42:37,760
Why did you add all that at the end?

605
00:42:38,310 --> 00:42:39,430
Didn't I tell you?

606
00:42:40,370 --> 00:42:42,100
We're nowhere near that stage.

607
00:42:42,830 --> 00:42:44,310
What did I say?

608
00:42:45,340 --> 00:42:46,870
I didn't mention you at all.

609
00:42:47,010 --> 00:42:48,410
Well, I did say one thing.

610
00:42:48,410 --> 00:42:49,610
I said I picked you up.

611
00:42:50,260 --> 00:42:51,060
Can I say that?

612
00:42:54,330 --> 00:42:55,270
You talked about

613
00:42:55,800 --> 00:42:57,530
"sorting out personal lives."

614
00:42:57,570 --> 00:42:58,030
Mom,

615
00:42:58,670 --> 00:43:00,070
you're overthinking it.

616
00:43:02,460 --> 00:43:04,660
I think you're the one overthinking it.

617
00:43:06,980 --> 00:43:08,190
Don't say anything like that later.
